To make pesto: In a food processor or blender, combine basil, garlic, salt, walnuts, Parmesan cheese, olive oil and butter. Process until a coarse paste is formed. Mushroom Pizza: Top each toasted muffin half with 1 tablespoon spaghetti sauce. Sprinkle with garlic salt and oregano. Top with 1 tablespoon drained canned mushroom slices -- then a scant 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese. Broil until done. Pepperoni Pizza: Top toasted muffin half with 1 tablespoon spaghetti sauce. Sprinkle with garlic salt and oregano. Top with three slices pepperoni sausage. Top with a scant 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese. Broil until done. Pesto Pizza: Top toasted muffin half with 1 tablespoon spaghetti sauce. Then add 1 1/2 teaspoons pesto sauce. Sprinkle lightly with chopped walnuts. Then top with scant 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese. Broil until done.